  <description type="morphology">Plants usually creeping and mat-forming; rhizomes relatively slender. Stems: submersed flexuous, to 60 cm; emersed ± ascending, 10–30(–45) cm. Leaf blades 7–23 × 0.3–2 mm. Peduncles 2–6 cm. Phyllaries 2–4 mm, margins minutely serrulate, faces glabrous. Corollas 2–3 mm (style branches conspicuously exserted). Cypselae 2–3.5 mm; pappi: scales indurate, broadly oblong, margins crenulate, apices obtuse, erose. 2n = 30.</description>
